**Privacy Policy — Diabetes Tracker**

Effective Date: June 8, 2026  
Last Updated: June 8, 2026

**1. Introduction**  
We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal and health-related information. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, when we share it, and your choices.

**2. Information We Collect**  
• Account information: name, email, hashed password, login and 2FA metadata.  
• Profile information: age, sex, weight, height, activity level, dietary type, allergies, cuisine preferences, ethnicity, and region.  
• Health data: glucose, blood pressure, HbA1c, weight, meal logs, adherence ratings, challenges, and reports.  
• AI inputs: ingredients and related context used for recipe and diet suggestions.  
• Technical data: limited diagnostics and app metadata for reliability and security.

**3. How We Use Data**  
We use your data to create and secure your account, provide analytics, generate diet guidance and health reports, improve app performance, and comply with legal obligations.

**4. Data Sharing**  
We do not sell your personal data. We may share data only with service providers needed to operate core features, with legal authorities when required by law, or during a business transfer.

**5. Data Security**  
We use reasonable safeguards including password hashing, authentication controls, and security monitoring. No system can guarantee absolute security.

**6. Data Retention**  
We retain data only as long as necessary to provide services, comply with law, and resolve disputes. Data is deleted or anonymized when no longer needed.

**7. Your Rights**  
Depending on your region, you may request access, correction, deletion, restriction, or portability of your data. Contact us to exercise your rights.

**8. Children's Privacy**  
This app is not intended for children under the minimum age required by local law without valid parental consent.

**9. Medical Disclaimer**  
This app supports wellness tracking and is not a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.

**10. Policy Updates**  
We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be notified in-app or via email.

